<p>The basic reproductive number, 
 <italic>R</italic>
 <sub>0</sub>, for the SEICR model can be calculated using the next-generation matrix method [
 <xref rid="pntd.0004676.ref017" ref-type="bibr">17</xref>,
 <xref rid="pntd.0004676.ref018" ref-type="bibr">18</xref>] and is given by 
 <disp-formula id="pntd.0004676.e002">
  <alternatives>
   <graphic xlink:href="pntd.0004676.e002.jpg" id="pntd.0004676.e002g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M2">
    <mrow>
     <mo> </mo>
     <msub>
      <mi>R</mi>
      <mn>0</mn>
     </msub>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mfrac>
      <mrow>
       <mi>β</mi>
       <msub>
        <mi>S</mi>
        <mn>0</mn>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mi>γ</mi>
     </mfrac>
     <mo>+</mo>
     <mfrac>
      <mrow>
       <mrow>
        <mo>(</mo>
        <mrow>
         <mn>1</mn>
         <mo>−</mo>
         <mi>f</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mo>)</mo>
       </mrow>
       <mo> </mo>
       <mi>p</mi>
       <mo> </mo>
       <msub>
        <mi>β</mi>
        <mi>s</mi>
       </msub>
       <mtext> </mtext>
      </mrow>
      <mi>α</mi>
     </mfrac>
     <mo>,</mo>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <italic>S</italic>
 <sub>0</sub> is the initial number of susceptible individuals (see 
 <xref ref-type="supplementary-material" rid="pntd.0004676.s006">S1 Appendix</xref>). When 
 <italic>α</italic> goes to infinity or either 
 <italic>β</italic>
 <sub>s</sub> = 0 or 
 <italic>p</italic> = 0, the equation reduces to the basic reproductive number in absence of sexual transmission: 
 <inline-formula id="pntd.0004676.e003">
  <alternatives>
   <graphic xlink:href="pntd.0004676.e003.jpg" id="pntd.0004676.e003g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M3">
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>R</mi>
      <mrow>
       <mn>0</mn>
       <mo>,</mo>
       <mi>N</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mfrac>
      <mrow>
       <mi>β</mi>
       <msub>
        <mi>S</mi>
        <mn>0</mn>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mi>γ</mi>
     </mfrac>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula>. Thus, the second term represents the contribution of sexual transmission from convalescent patients to the overall 
 <italic>R</italic>
 <sub>0</sub>: 
 <inline-formula id="pntd.0004676.e004">
  <alternatives>
   <graphic xlink:href="pntd.0004676.e004.jpg" id="pntd.0004676.e004g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M4">
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>R</mi>
      <mrow>
       <mn>0</mn>
       <mo>,</mo>
       <mi>C</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mfrac>
      <mrow>
       <mrow>
        <mo>(</mo>
        <mrow>
         <mn>1</mn>
         <mo>−</mo>
         <mi>f</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mo>)</mo>
       </mrow>
       <mo> </mo>
       <mi>p</mi>
       <mo> </mo>
       <msub>
        <mi>β</mi>
        <mi>s</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mi>α</mi>
     </mfrac>
     <mtext> </mtext>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula>.
</p>
